# accessibility-baseline.mdc

- Interactive controls must be keyboard operable; use native `button` and `a` (with `href`) where possible.
- Icon-only buttons and icon links must have an accessible name (`aria-label` or visible text).
- Form inputs must be associated with labels (visible `<label>` or `aria-labelledby`).
- Decorative images should use `alt=""`; informative images need descriptive `alt` text.
- Do not rely on color alone to convey required state or errors — include text or icons with semantics.
